<h4>Activity</h4>
<p>A college student is choosing between two data plans for her new cell phone. Both plans include an allowance of 2 gigabytes of data per month. The monthly cost of each option can be seen as a function and represented with an equation:</p>
<ul>
<li>Option A: \(A(x)=60\)</li>
<li>Option B: \(B(x)=10x+25\)</li>
</ul>
<p>In each function, the input, \(x\), represents the gigabytes of data used <em>over</em> the monthly allowance.</p>
<p>The student decides to find the cost of each option when she exceeds the 2 gigabytes of data allowed each month. Use the function rules to help her compare the data plans. </p>
